description: Retrieves information about a Timestream for InfluxDB cluster.

parameters.name: dbClusterId
parameters.description: Service-generated unique identifier of the DB cluster to retrieve.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: Service-generated unique identifier of the DB cluster to retrieve.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: Customer-supplied name of the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: endpoint
nested_items.description: The endpoint used to connect to the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster for write and read operations.

nested_items.name: readerEndpoint
nested_items.description: The endpoint used to connect to the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster for read-only operations.

nested_items.name: port
nested_items.description: The port number on which InfluxDB accepts connections.

nested_items.name: deploymentType
nested_items.description: Deployment type of the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: dbInstanceType
nested_items.description: The Timestream for InfluxDB instance type that InfluxDB runs on.

nested_items.name: networkType
nested_items.description: Specifies whether the network type of the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster is IPv4, which can communicate over IPv4 protocol only, or DUAL, which can communicate over both IPv4 and IPv6 protocols.

nested_items.name: dbStorageType
nested_items.description: The Timestream for InfluxDB DB storage type that InfluxDB stores data on.

nested_items.name: allocatedStorage
nested_items.description: The amount of storage allocated for your DB storage type (in gibibytes).

nested_items.name: publiclyAccessible
nested_items.description: Indicates if the DB cluster has a public IP to facilitate access from outside the VPC.

nested_items.name: dbParameterGroupIdentifier
nested_items.description: The ID of the DB parameter group assigned to your DB cluster.

nested_items.name: logDeliveryConfiguration
nested_items.description: Configuration for sending InfluxDB engine logs to send to specified S3 bucket.

nested_items.name: s3Configuration
nested_items.description: Configuration for S3 bucket log delivery.

nested_items.name: bucketName
nested_items.description: The name of the S3 bucket to deliver logs to.

nested_items.name: enabled
nested_items.description: Indicates whether log delivery to the S3 bucket is enabled.

nested_items.name: influxAuthParametersSecretArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Secrets Manager secret containing the initial InfluxDB authorization parameters. The secret value is a JSON formatted key-value pair holding InfluxDB authorization values: organization, bucket, username, and password.

nested_items.name: vpcSubnetIds
nested_items.description: A list of VPC subnet IDs associated with the DB cluster.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: vpcSecurityGroupIds
nested_items.description: A list of VPC security group IDs associated with the DB cluster.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: failoverMode
nested_items.description: The configured failover mode for the DB cluster.
